comments.body:
There are several instances I can think of where PowerShell users would find this useful. As well as a tool for internal development.

This would be great passing a [PSObject] to a specific overload in C# a great toolkit for future work in module builders.

[ValidateType([int], [int32], [string], [float])]
PSObject foo;

where you could take 
var x = foo.BaseObject;
calloverload(x);

This would be really good for that.

Also could also allow for type casting capabilities for desired type's without a need for a switch case or try catch all your error handling would be done at a validation level.

I think this would be invaluable.
